        "author": {
          "name": "Parinay Kondekar",
          "email": "parinay_kondekar@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2014-09-04 11:38:10.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Parinay Kondekar",
          "email": "parinay_kondekar@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2014-09-04 11:43:09.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-5582  mgc: Client fails to mount the filesystem",
        "message": "LU-5582  mgc: Client fails to mount the filesystem\n\nlustre_start_mgc() creates MGC device, if error happens later on\nll_fill_super(), this device is still attached, leaving a stale entry.\nSubsequent lustre client mount attempts, fail, with EEXIST (-17).\n\nThis change, makes sure, such scenarios are taken care of with\nmgc_precleanup() remvoving llog subsystem with any stale entry.\n\nThus the subsequent mount attempts succeed without any errors.\n\nmgc_precleanup asks the mgc_requeue_thread to do cleanup/shutdown\nnot only for last MGC entry but for every MGC being shutdown.\n\nWhen mgc_precleanup() kicks the requeue thread - it does not start\nimmediately but _waits_ for some amount of time magically calculated\nwith 'lwi'. As long as RQ_STOP is not set before the kick we added\nonly expired timeout makes mgc_requeue_thread() to continue.\n\nThe flag RQ_MGC_PRECLEANUP is introduced to reduce this slowness.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-1524\nChange-Id: Icf68ec9a3e479a7a56969522935299d392f9e8cb\nSigned-off-by: Vladimir Saveliev <vladimir_saveliev@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Parinay Kondekar <parinay_kondekar@xyratex.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
